CSS system
CSS
:root {
  --bg: #f6f7fb;
  --surface: #ffffff;
  --surface-2: #f0f2f7;
  --border: #e5e7eb;
  --text: #0a0e1a;
  --muted: #667085;
  --muted-2: #98a2b3;
  --ink: #0a0e1a;
  --green: #12b981;
  --green-bg: #ecfdf3;
  --green-border: #a6f4c5;
  --shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(16, 24, 40, 0.04), 0 1px 3px rgba(16, 24, 40, 0.1);
}

* { box-sizing: border-box; }
html, body { height: 100%; margin: 0; }
body {
  font-family: Inter, system-ui, sans-serif;
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--text);
}

.dm-app {
  height: 100%;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.dm-topnav {
  height: 60px;
  background: var(--surface);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 0 20px;
}

.dm-brand {
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}

.dm-mainnav {
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
}

.dm-mainnav button,
.dm-record-actions button,
.dm-proof-actions button,
.dm-tabs button,
.dm-sidebar-filters button {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  background: var(--surface);
  color: var(--text);
  height: 36px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 0 14px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.dm-mainnav .nav-active,
.dm-tabs .tab-active,
.dm-sidebar-filters .filter-active {
  background: var(--surface-2);
  font-weight: 600;
}

.dm-user {
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 14px;
}

.dm-shell {
  flex: 1;
  min-height: 0;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 320px minmax(0, 1fr) 340px;
}

.dm-sidebar,
.dm-proofrail {
  background: var(--surface);
  border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  min-height: 0;
  overflow: auto;
}

.dm-proofrail {
  border-right: none;
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 20px;
}

.dm-sidebar {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.dm-sidebar-search,
.dm-sidebar-filters,
.dm-record-groups,
.dm-sidebar-footer {
  padding: 16px;
}

.dm-sidebar-search input {
  width: 100%;
  height: 40px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 0 12px;
  background: var(--surface-2);
}

.dm-sidebar-filters {
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
  padding-top: 0;
}

.dm-record-groups {
  flex: 1;
  min-height: 0;
  overflow: auto;
  padding-top: 0;
}

.dm-group-label {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.dm-record-row {
  width: 100%;
  text-align: left;
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  background: transparent;
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 12px;
  cursor: pointer;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.dm-record-row:hover {
  background: var(--surface-2);
}

.dm-record-row-active {
  background: var(--surface-2);
  border-color: var(--border);
}

.dm-record-title {
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
  line-height: 1.3;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.dm-record-meta,
.dm-record-preview,
.dm-sidebar-status,
.dm-sidebar-source {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
}

.dm-sidebar-footer {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 6px;
}

.dm-main {
  min-width: 0;
  min-height: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 20px;
  gap: 16px;
}

.dm-record-header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 20px;
}

.dm-record-heading h1 {
  margin: 0 0 8px 0;
  font-size: 28px;
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
}

.dm-record-submeta {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 8px 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 13px;
}

.dm-status-ok {
  color: #067647;
  background: var(--green-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--green-border);
  border-radius: 999px;
  padding: 2px 10px;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.dm-record-actions {
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
}

.dm-tabs {
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
}

.dm-tabpanel {
  flex: 1;
  min-height: 0;
  overflow: auto;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 14px;
}

.dm-entry {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 14px 16px;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow);
}

.dm-entry-user {
  background: var(--ink);
  color: white;
  border-color: var(--ink);
}

.dm-entry-agent {
  background: var(--surface);
}

.dm-entry-label {
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
  color: inherit;
  opacity: 0.8;
}

.dm-entry-body {
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.dm-entry-time {
  margin-top: 10px;
  font-size: 12px;
  opacity: 0.75;
}

.dm-proof-header {
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.dm-proof-checks {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
}

.dm-proof-check {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 10px;
  background: var(--surface-2);
  padding: 12px 14px;
  font-size: 14px;
}

.dm-proof-check.ok::before {
  content: "✓ ";
  color: var(--green);
  font-weight: 700;
}

.dm-proof-summary {
  margin-top: 16px;
  padding: 14px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  background: var(--green-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--green-border);
  color: #067647;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.dm-proof-actions {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 8px;
  margin-top: 16px;
}
Claude-style adaptations you should keep

From Claude Console, keep:

split-pane reading model

clear left navigation

action buttons near title

right-side contextual panel

calm spacing

understated controls

Do not keep:

dev-centric transcript/debug framing

provider-heavy branding in the main content

setup/config as the center of the UI

Suggested next implementation order
Backend

add Anthropic proxy routes

commit request + response steps

add per-session parent linkage

map proxy sessions into dashboard records

Frontend

replace current record page shell with the layout above

make Record the default tab

move verification into dedicated right rail and proof tab

move raw JSON out of the default view

keep share/export visible at all times

If you want, next I can write the actual Express + fetch + dm.commit integration using your current route naming style, or the full dashboard.html file as a drop-in mock.

